# 2 - urban
P.append(passage("j8_urban_004",
    "The Grammar of Convenience Stores", "便利店的语法", 8,
    "便利店是城市的标点符号——它不构成主语或谓语，但没有它，城市的句子就会变得不可读。我住的小区周围一公里以内有七家便利店，每一家都有自己不同的「语法功能」。巷口那家是「逗号」，早晨上班的人在这里暂停两分钟，买一杯咖啡和一个饭团，然后继续赶路。公司楼下那家是「分号」，午休时承接上半天与下半天之间的过渡，人们在这里买一份便当和一瓶水。地铁站旁边那家是「连接词」，把地下交通系统和地面生活无缝衔接。而我家楼下那家深夜还亮着灯的小店，是「句号」——一天结束前最后一个文明的据点，你可以在这里买到明天早餐的牛奶和今晚失眠时可能需要的零食。便利店的本质不是零售，而是一种空间服务：它填充了城市肌理中那些微小的空隙——太晚了超市已关门，太早了餐厅还没开，太累了不想自己做饭。它永远在你需要的时候存在，却从不要求你的注意力。这是一种极其谦逊的商业形态。",
    "Biànlìdiàn shì chéngshì de biāodiǎn fúhào——tā bù gòuchéng zhǔyǔ huò wèiyǔ, dàn méiyǒu tā, chéngshì de jùzi jiù huì biàn de bùkě dú.",
    "Convenience stores are a city's punctuation marks—they don't form subject or predicate, but without them the city's sentences become unreadable. Within one kilometer of my neighborhood there are seven, each with its own 'grammatical function.' The one at the alley entrance is a 'comma,' where morning commuters pause two minutes for coffee and a rice ball before continuing. The one below the office is a 'semicolon,' bridging the transition between morning and afternoon during lunch break. The one by the subway station is a 'conjunction,' seamlessly linking underground transit and surface life. The one below my apartment still lit late at night is a 'period'—the last outpost of civilization before day's end, where you buy tomorrow's breakfast milk and snacks for tonight's potential insomnia. The essence of convenience stores is not retail but spatial service: they fill the tiny gaps in urban texture—too late for supermarkets, too early for restaurants, too tired to cook. They exist whenever you need them, yet never demand your attention. This is an extraordinarily humble form of commerce.",
    mc("作者将便利店比作「标点符号」，核心含义是什么？",
       "What is the core meaning of comparing convenience stores to punctuation marks?",
       [o("便利店很小，不起眼","biànlìdiàn hěn xiǎo, bù qǐyǎn","Convenience stores are small and inconspicuous"),
        o("便利店虽不是城市的核心功能，但没有它城市生活就无法流畅运转","biànlìdiàn suī bú shì chéngshì de héxīn gōngnéng, dàn méiyǒu tā chéngshì shēnghuó jiù wúfǎ liúchàng yùnzhuǎn","Though not a city's core function, without them urban life cannot run smoothly",True),
        o("便利店的数量太多了","biànlìdiàn de shùliàng tài duō le","There are too many convenience stores"),
        o("便利店应该在固定时间营业","biànlìdiàn yīnggāi zài gùdìng shíjiān yíngyè","Convenience stores should operate at fixed times")], 0.45),
    mc("作者为什么说便利店是「极其谦逊的商业形态」？",
       "Why does the author call convenience stores an 'extraordinarily humble form of commerce'?",
       [o("便利店的利润很低","biànlìdiàn de lìrùn hěn dī","Convenience store profits are low"),
        o("它在你需要时存在却从不要求你的注意力","tā zài nǐ xūyào shí cúnzài què cóng bù yāoqiú nǐ de zhùyìlì","It exists when you need it but never demands your attention",True),
        o("便利店的装修很简朴","biànlìdiàn de zhuāngxiū hěn jiǎnpǔ","Convenience store decor is simple"),
        o("便利店不做广告","biànlìdiàn bú zuò guǎnggào","Convenience stores don't advertise")], 0.45),
    mc("深夜便利店被比作「句号」的原因是什么？",
       "Why is the late-night convenience store compared to a 'period'?",
       [o("它是一天中最后一个可以获得服务的文明据点","tā shì yī tiān zhōng zuìhòu yī gè kěyǐ huòdé fúwù de wénmíng jùdiǎn","It is the last civilized outpost where you can get service before day's end",True),
        o("它每天在固定时间关门","tā měi tiān zài gùdìng shíjiān guānmén","It closes at a fixed time every day"),
        o("它的商品种类最少","tā de shāngpǐn zhǒnglèi zuì shǎo","It has the fewest product varieties"),
        o("它是最后一家还在营业的商店","tā shì zuìhòu yī jiā hái zài yíngyè de shāngdiàn","It's the last store still operating")], 0.4)))

# 3 - inst
P.append(passage("j8_inst_003",
    "The Post Office as Living Museum", "作为活体博物馆的邮局", 8,
    "我家附近有一间建于一九五二年的老邮局，至今仍在营业。走进去的第一感觉是时间在这里流速不同。柜台上方的电子叫号屏是唯一的现代元素，其余一切——水磨石地面、木质柜台、铁栏杆窗口——都保留着半个世纪前的样子。工作人员的操作方式也明显更慢：她们用手写体填单子，用橡皮图章逐一盖邮戳，把包裹放在一台老式台秤上称重。排队的人大多是五十岁以上的老人，他们来寄信、取汇款、交水电费——这些事情在手机上都能完成，但他们坚持亲自来。我问过一位每月都来交电费的陈大爷为什么不用手机。他说：「在手机上按几下就完了，太快了，感觉不像真的做了一件事。来这里，排个队，跟窗口的小姑娘说说话，拿到一张盖了章的收据，这才踏实。」邮局对这些老人来说不是一个办理业务的场所，而是一个仪式空间——他们用排队和盖章来确认自己仍然在这个社会系统中占有一个位置。当效率成为唯一的价值标准时，我们可能忘记了：对有些人来说，慢本身就是一种存在的证明。",
    "Wǒ jiā fùjìn yǒu yī jiān jiàn yú yī jiǔ wǔ èr nián de lǎo yóujú, zhìjīn réng zài yíngyè. Zǒu jìnqù de dì yī gǎnjué shì shíjiān zài zhèlǐ liúsù bùtóng.",
    "Near my home there's a post office built in 1952, still operating. Walking in, the first sensation is that time flows differently here. The electronic number display above the counter is the only modern element; everything else—terrazzo floor, wooden counter, iron-barred windows—remains as it was half a century ago. Staff operate noticeably slower: they fill forms by hand, stamp each postmark with rubber stamps, weigh parcels on an old-fashioned scale. Most people in line are over fifty, coming to mail letters, collect remittances, pay utility bills—all doable on a phone, yet they insist on coming in person. I asked Uncle Chen, who comes monthly to pay his electric bill, why not use his phone. He said: 'On the phone you tap a few times and it's done. Too fast. Doesn't feel like you've actually done something. Coming here, standing in line, chatting with the girl at the window, getting a stamped receipt—that feels real.' For these elderly people the post office is not a place to conduct business but a ritual space—they use queuing and stamps to confirm they still occupy a position in the social system. When efficiency becomes the only standard of value, we may forget: for some people, slowness itself is proof of existence.",
    mc("陈大爷坚持亲自去邮局交电费的根本原因是什么？",
       "What is Uncle Chen's fundamental reason for going to the post office in person?",
       [o("他不会用手机","tā bú huì yòng shǒujī","He doesn't know how to use a phone"),
        o("亲身参与的仪式感让他确认自己仍存在于社会系统中","qīnshēn cānyù de yíshìgǎn ràng tā quèrèn zìjǐ réng cúnzài yú shèhuì xìtǒng zhōng","The ritual of personal participation confirms he still exists within the social system",True),
        o("邮局的服务费更便宜","yóujú de fúwùfèi gèng piányí","Post office service fees are cheaper"),
        o("他不信任网上支付的安全性","tā bú xìnrèn wǎngshàng zhīfù de ānquánxìng","He doesn't trust online payment security")], 0.5),
    mc("作者说「慢本身就是一种存在的证明」，这句话的深层含义是什么？",
       "What is the deeper meaning of 'slowness itself is proof of existence'?",
       [o("效率不是唯一的价值标准，参与过程本身对人有确认存在的意义","xiàolǜ bú shì wéiyī de jiàzhí biāozhǔn, cānyù guòchéng běnshēn duì rén yǒu quèrèn cúnzài de yìyì","Efficiency is not the only value standard; the process of participation itself confirms one's existence",True),
        o("老年人动作慢是正常的","lǎonián rén dòngzuò màn shì zhèngcháng de","It's normal for elderly people to move slowly"),
        o("邮局应该保持传统做法","yóujú yīnggāi bǎochí chuántǒng zuòfǎ","Post offices should maintain traditional practices"),
        o("现代社会节奏太快","xiàndài shèhuì jiézòu tài kuài","Modern society's pace is too fast")], 0.55),
    mc("作者将邮局称为「活体博物馆」，最可能的原因是：",
       "Why does the author call the post office a 'living museum'?",
       [o("邮局的建筑有历史价值","yóujú de jiànzhù yǒu lìshǐ jiàzhí","The post office building has historical value"),
        o("它保留着过去的物质形态和运作方式，同时仍在服务于当下的人群","tā bǎoliú zhe guòqù de wùzhì xíngtài hé yùnzuò fāngshì, tóngshí réng zài fúwù yú dāngxià de rénqún","It preserves past material forms and operating methods while still serving present-day people",True),
        o("邮局里有很多旧物展示","yóujú lǐ yǒu hěn duō jiùwù zhǎnshì","The post office displays many old items"),
        o("很少有人再去邮局了","hěn shǎo yǒu rén zài qù yóujú le","Few people go to the post office anymore")], 0.45)))

