P.append(passage("j8_mystery_003",
    "The Notebook in the Used Bookstore", "旧书店里的笔记本", 8,
    "我在一家旧书店的角落里发现了一个皮面笔记本，夹在两本七十年代的工程手册之间。笔记本没有署名，也没有日期，但从纸张的泛黄程度和钢笔字迹的墨色来看，至少有三十年的历史。里面的内容让我困惑了好几天。前半部分是工整的植物学笔记：各种花卉的拉丁名、生长周期、适宜土壤，配有精确的手绘插图。后半部分突然变了——字迹变得潦草，内容变成了断断续续的句子，像是日记但又不完全是。「今天又下雨了，第三周了。」「她说得对，我确实不了解自己。」「栀子花开了，但不是去年那株。」「决定不再去那个地方了。」这些句子之间没有明确的因果关系，就像散落在地上的拼图碎片。我试图把它们拼成一个完整的故事：一个热爱植物学的人，经历了某种情感变故，笔记本从此成了一个无人对话的出口。但我知道这只是我的推测。旧书店老板说这本笔记本是从一位遗孀那里收来的废品堆中捡出来的。一个人的内心世界就这样变成了一件标价五元的二手商品。",
    "Wǒ zài yī jiā jiù shūdiàn de jiǎoluò lǐ fāxiàn le yī gè pí miàn bǐjìběn, jiā zài liǎng běn qīshí niándài de gōngchéng shǒucè zhījiān.",
    "I found a leather-bound notebook in the corner of a used bookstore, sandwiched between two 1970s engineering manuals. No name, no date, but the yellowing paper and pen ink color suggested at least thirty years. The contents puzzled me for days. The first half was meticulous botanical notes: Latin names of flowers, growth cycles, suitable soils, with precise hand-drawn illustrations. The second half changed abruptly—handwriting became scrawled, content shifted to fragmentary sentences, like a diary but not quite. 'Rained again today, third week.' 'She was right, I really don't understand myself.' 'The gardenia bloomed, but it's not last year's plant.' 'Decided not to go to that place anymore.' These sentences had no clear causal links, like puzzle pieces scattered on the floor. I tried assembling them into a complete story: a botany lover who experienced some emotional upheaval, the notebook becoming an outlet with no listener. But I know that's only my speculation. The bookstore owner said the notebook was salvaged from a pile of discards bought from a widow. A person's inner world had become a five-yuan secondhand item.",
    mc("笔记本前后两部分的变化暗示了什么？",
       "What does the change between the notebook's two halves suggest?",
       [o("写笔记的人换了一支笔","xiě bǐjì de rén huàn le yī zhī bǐ","The writer switched pens"),
        o("写作者经历了某种情感变故，从有序的学术记录转向了无序的内心表达","xiězuòzhě jīnglì le mǒu zhǒng qínggǎn biàngù, cóng yǒuxù de xuéshù jìlù zhuǎnxiàng le wúxù de nèixīn biǎodá","The writer experienced emotional upheaval, shifting from orderly academic notes to disordered inner expression",True),
        o("笔记本的后半部分是另一个人写的","bǐjìběn de hòu bànbùfen shì lìng yī gè rén xiě de","The second half was written by a different person"),
        o("植物学课程结束了","zhíwùxué kèchéng jiéshù le","The botany course ended")], 0.5),
    mc("作者说「一个人的内心世界变成了五元的二手商品」，表达了什么情感？",
       "What emotion does 'a person's inner world became a five-yuan secondhand item' express?",
       [o("对旧书店定价太低的不满","duì jiù shūdiàn dìngjià tài dī de bùmǎn","Dissatisfaction with the bookstore's low pricing"),
        o("对个人精神遗产被遗忘和贬值的惋惜","duì gèrén jīngshén yíchǎn bèi yíwàng hé biǎnzhí de wǎnxī","Wistfulness over personal spiritual legacy being forgotten and devalued",True),
        o("对收藏旧物的兴趣","duì shōucáng jiùwù de xìngqù","Interest in collecting old things"),
        o("对遗孀处理遗物方式的批评","duì yíshuǎng chǔlǐ yíwù fāngshì de pīpíng","Criticism of how the widow handled the belongings")], 0.55),
    mc("作者对笔记本中断续句子的处理方式反映了什么？",
       "What does the author's approach to the notebook's fragmentary sentences reflect?",
       [o("他是一个职业侦探","tā shì yī gè zhíyè zhēntàn","He is a professional detective"),
        o("人类倾向于从碎片中构建完整叙事，即使是推测","rénlèi qīngxiàng yú cóng suìpiàn zhōng gòujiàn wánzhěng xùshì, jíshǐ shì tuīcè","Humans tend to construct complete narratives from fragments, even speculatively",True),
        o("旧书店里经常能找到有价值的东西","jiù shūdiàn lǐ jīngcháng néng zhǎodào yǒu jiàzhí de dōngxi","Valuable things are often found in used bookstores"),
        o("他想把这个笔记本写成小说","tā xiǎng bǎ zhège bǐjìběn xiě chéng xiǎoshuō","He wants to turn the notebook into a novel")], 0.45)))

